AD_FIELD.NAME: Template Line
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Unique line identifier
AD_FIELD.HELP: Unique identifier for each template line record.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Provider
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Print provider responsible for processing a label request.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Provider configuration that should handle the printing action. The chosen record determines: -Which credentials and URLs are used. -Which implementation class is loaded (via the Providers Implementation). -Which printers appear in the printer selector pop-up.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Client
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Client for this installation.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Print URL
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: HTTP endpoint to which label print-jobs are posted.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Specify the full URL that accepts print requests for this provider (e.g. https://api.printnode.com/printjobs). During printing, the framework calls the provider’s Java implementation, which posts the rendered file (PDF, ZPL, etc.) to this POST URL using the credentials stored in API Key.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Name
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A non-unique identifier for a record/document often used as a search tool.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A more descriptive identifier (that does need to be unique) of a record/document that is used as a default search option along with the search key (that is unique and mostly shorter). It is up to 60 characters in length.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Organization
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Organizational entity within client
AD_FIELD.HELP: An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Refreshprinters
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Refreshes the printer list from the selected Print Provider.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Click Refresh Printers to synchronise Etendo with the external middleware (e.g., PrintNode, CUPS gateway) configured in Print Providers. The system will: 1. Use the provider’s Printers GET URL and API Key. 2. Load the mapped Provider Implementation (System Admin sets this in Providers Implementation). 3. Fetch the current fleet of printers and upsert rows in the Printers grid.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Active
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_FIELD.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_FIELD.HELP: Paste the exact API-level credential issued by the provider’s platform (e.g. PrintNode “API Key” or CUPS gateway token).

AD_FIELD.NAME: Providers Implementation
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Record identifier for Providers Implementation entries.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Primary key for Providers Implementation records.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Search Key
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A fast method for finding a particular record.
AD_FIELD.HELP:
A search key allows for a fast method of finding a particular record. If you leave the search key empty, the system automatically creates a numeric number originating from a document sequence defined in the "Document Sequence" window. The sequence naming convention follows a rule "DocumentNo_TableName", where TableName is the actual name of the database table (e.g. C_Order).
Usually, company's internal identifiers for various records (products, customers, etc) are stored here.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Printers URL
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: HTTP endpoint that returns the provider’s printer list.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Enter the absolute URL (e.g. https://api.printnode.com/printers) used to retrieve printers for this provider. The Update Printers process issues an authenticated GET request to this address. Include any required path, port or query-string; do not append API-key parameters—authentication is handled by the implementation class.
